vip.floatationdevice.guilded4j

Class G4JClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • vip.floatationdevice.guilded4j.G4JClient

  • public class G4JClient
extends java.lang.Object
    Guilded4J's main component, can send HTTP requests to the API, receive WebSocket events and post them as GuildedEvents.
    See Also:
    G4JWebSocketClient, GuildedEvent

      • createChannelMessage

        public ChatMessage createChannelMessage(java.lang.String channelId,
                                        java.lang.String content,

                                        java.lang.Boolean isPrivate,
                                        java.lang.Boolean isSilent)
        Create a channel message.
        https://www.guilded.gg/docs/api/chat/ChannelMessageCreate
        Parameters:
        channelId - The ID of the channel.
        content - The message content to create.
        embeds - Rich content sections associated with the message (can be null).
        replyMessageIds - The ID of the message(s) to reply to (maximum of 5, null if not replying).
        isPrivate - If set, this message will only be seen by those mentioned or replied to.
        isSilent - If set, this message will not notify any mentioned users or roles.
        Returns:
        The newly created message's ChatMessage object.
        Throws:
        GuildedException - if Guilded API returned an error JSON string.
        cn.hutool.core.io.IORuntimeException - if an error occurred while sending HTTP request.
